item.title: Jbirdscape Project Thread
item.dc:creator: @Pure_Slay Pure Slay
item.description:
@Pure_Slay wrote:

[quote=“jcrane164, post:30, topic:429322”]Since you obviously think you know what your talking about please prove to me what skills you have? On top of that your a retard for saying what you just said. Efficiency could be use for one small part of that code. It doesnt mean the entire system works correctly yet. There are tons of different ways to make certain code work a proper way. There are obviously better ways than others. That meaning there are different types of efficient. You dont even know me and have never glanced at my code nor logged on my server to see how things run. So if you wish to troll go else where.

EDIT: I seen your sig thread, its pretty nice but it still doesnt change what i said.[/quote]

I was more or less telling you to stop talking such a big story on your skills. Your comment is basically saying you never write bad code, but I guarantee your code is not up to standards of a professional programmer. But hey, prove me wrong, post some open source code so that I can critique it.

Also, I wouldn’t bother to comment on my skills. They greatly excel a majority of others on multiple levels. I’ve done time with rsps and moved on. I’ve done packet identification, login on newer protocols, and heavy refactoring in the client (since rsps is most likely the only thing you do, I will only provide examples from that). I’ve also do more than one language for programming. I don’t remember posting anywhere in my comment that I was a goddess, as if I wanted to sound better then you, I would just sum up this paragraph and had originally wrote it.

It is better to be modest when bragging a shit storm about yourself, unless you can back it up. I wouldn’t ever go as far as you have by stating that my code is never messy and always efficient. Hell, tons of programmers rewrite things hundreds of times to improve it. You barely ever write a finished design on your first try.
